HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 262
BY REPRESENTATIVE MOORE
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Tre'Shun
McGee.
WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the untimely passing of
Tre'Shun McGee; and
WHEREAS, Tre'Shun was born on January 19, 2012, in Monroe, Louisiana, to
Danielle Jones and Travis McGee; he was an intelligent, kind, and energetic young man who
made an impact on all who knew him; and
WHEREAS, Tre'Shun was known for his smile, loving personality, and goofiness;
and
WHEREAS, Tre'Shun attended Martin Luther King Jr. Junior High School, where
he played basketball, ran track, and was a member of the school band; he was a bright
student and member of the Beta Club, where he served in the role of historian; and
WHEREAS, Tre'Shun loved sports and playing video games, especially Fortnite and
2K; and
WHEREAS, Tre'Shun McGee leaves to cherish his memory three dedicated sisters,
Makaela, Kaeyln, and Shontasia; four other sisters; four brothers; maternal grandmother,
Carrie Jones; maternal grandfather, Gregory Owens; paternal grandmother, Pamela McGee;
paternal grandfather, Matthew Cooper; favorite aunt, Stormye Jones; two favorite uncles,
Christopher Jones and Damion Jones; and a host of cousins and extended relatives; he will
be deeply missed, but the legacy of his loving spirit shall live on in the hearts and minds of
those who were privileged to have known and loved him.
